## colors.rpy - Color scheme reference
##
## NOTE: Color definitions have been moved to gui.rpy for editor compatibility.
## Use the Preset Editor's Game Config tab to edit colors.
##
## This file is kept for reference. All active color definitions are in gui.rpy.
##
## Related files: gui.rpy, styles.rpy

## Colors defined in gui.rpy (editable via Game Config):
##
## Primary Colors:
##   gui.accent_color - Highlights, selections, important elements
##   gui.idle_color - Default state for interactive elements
##   gui.idle_small_color - Smaller/secondary text
##   gui.hover_color - Hovered elements
##   gui.selected_color - Currently selected items
##   gui.insensitive_color - Disabled elements
##   gui.muted_color - De-emphasized text
##   gui.hover_muted_color - Muted hover state
##
## Text Colors:
##   gui.text_color - Main text color
##   gui.interface_text_color - Menu/UI text
##   gui.dialogue_text_color - Dialogue box text
##   gui.name_text_color - Character name color
##
## UI Element Colors:
##   gui.frame_color - Frame backgrounds
##   gui.bar_color - Unfilled bar portions
##   gui.bar_full_color - Filled bar portions
##   gui.scrollbar_color - Scrollbar idle
##   gui.scrollbar_hover_color - Scrollbar hovered
##   gui.slider_color - Slider idle
##   gui.slider_hover_color - Slider hovered
